&lt;h3&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Data Analyst, Providers plays a critical role in partnering with cross-functional leaders to shape and deliver Octave&#39;s provider analytics strategy. In this role, you will be responsible for defining key provider and clinical performance metrics, generating insights, and building scalable data models and analytics products that empower teams to make data-informed decisions. The ideal candidate is both a thinker and a doer who thrives in ambiguity, deeply understands clinical and operational workflows, and is passionate about using data to improve patient outcomes and provider performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Duties &amp;amp; Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with clinical, operations, product, and engineering teams to identify key business problems and develop analytics solutions that drive growth and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop dashboards, reporting, and self-service tools that enable teams to monitor performance and make data-informed decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate insights and recommendations clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders and guide understanding of clinical quality and provider product needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with peers to design and maintain data models within Octave’s data warehouse to ensure reliable, scalable datasets that support analytics across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI tools as a core part of daily work (drafting, research, iteration) to improve efficiency, quality, and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical and problem-solving skills to translate complex clinical workflows and operational processes into scalable data and reporting frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to connect data insights to business strategy and communicate findings clearly to a wide range of audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-directed curiosity; a knack for asking the right questions and comfortably navigating ambiguity to answer them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to confidently and independently drive projects from conception to completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of clinical data, including treatment modalities, clinical notes, patient assessment data, and care pathways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of improving clinical KPIs, such as patient engagement, treatment adherence, outcome measurement, and operational efficiency through data-driven insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of healthcare data privacy regulations (e.g., HIPAA) and best practices for handling sensitive patient information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort using AI tools in day-to-day workflows, with a willingness to continuously rethink and improve how work gets done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity and openness to experimenting with new tools and approaches; prior experience with AI tools is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
